    "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nThe output file formats tend to use host memory buffers in a fairly predictable way.  We cache the data on the CPU until the batch is done being written and then we copy it out to the output stream or drop it.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/issues/9862 should let limit the total memory used when allocating the data. But we need to make each of the buffers [spillable](https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/issues/8882) as they are handed to us and add in retry as needed.  After that it should just work how we want it to.\r\n\r\n###  Tasks\r\n- [x] JNI call path allocate_host_buffer must use HostMemoryAllocator https://github.com/rapidsai/cudf/issues/13940\r\n- [x] https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids-jni/pull/1377\r\n- [x] Transition spark-rapids to pass an allocator of spillable host memory buffers to output file formats\r\n\r\n```[tasklist]\r\n### Tasks\r\n- [ ] Use CPU OOM mode to veriyf spillability in NDS\r\n```\r\n",
